This python script does the following:
1. Parses .txt files 
2. Joins the .txt files 
3. Cleans the strings returned from the .txt files using regular expressions
4. Isolates Anthony Kennedy's speech in the strings 
5. Reads in the WUSTL (Washington University in St. Louis) SCOTUS (Supreme Court of the United States) database 
6. Joins Justice Kennedy's speech by SCOTUS case ID to the WUSTL database 
7. Returns two types of Pandas DataFrames: a) where text is stemmed or b) where text is not stemmed
